The Governor of Ebonyi State, Chief David Umahi on Monday announced the suspension of his Special Assistant, SA, on Project Monitoring, Ebonyi South Zone, Engr. Felix Ottah, for lack of commitment and seriousness in the discharge of his duties. Ottah was suspended barely three weeks after he was inaugurated by the Governor at the exco-chambers in Government House, Abakaliki. Recall that Ottah was the second person to be suspended after the indefinite suspension of another aide, one Francis Nweze, SA to the governor on Project and Documentation for same offence. The suspension was made known in a press statement signed by the Secretary to the State Government, SSG /Coordinating Commissioner, Dr. Ugbala Kenneth Igwe. The statement reads in part, “The Special Assistant to the Governor on Project Monitoring (Ebonyi South Zone), Engr. Felix Ottah is hereby suspended indefinitely from office with immediate effect. “This indefinite suspension from office is as a result of glaring demonstration of lack of commitment and seriousness in the discharge of his official duties. “The SA is therefore directed to hand over all Government properties in his possession to the Office of the Secretary to the State Government on or before close of work Tuesday 27th August, 2019,” he stated. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.